# 200 = rewrite (proxy), keeping the browser URL as /b/:id so the page's JS can
# read the id from the path. Destinations are the EXTENSIONLESS clean paths —
# pointing at /book.html triggers Cloudflare Pages' automatic .html→clean-URL
# 308 redirect, which drops the :id (bit us: shared links landed on /book with
# no id and showed the "not available" fallback).
/b/*   /book   200
/a/*   /author   200
/p/*   /publisher   200
